    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSetting the `vim.g.health` variable to `{ style = 'float' }` makes the `Health` buffer created upon `:checkhealth` be a floating window, which I like because it does not open a new tabpage or switch my main buffer. The window, in this case, is like a dropdown: horizontally centered within the \"full\" nvim window, and aligned at the top.\n\nCalling `:checkhealth` from a help buffer instead places the floating window at the top-left of the \"full\" nvim screen.\n\nHere is a `minimal.lua` reproduction file:\n\n```lua\nvim.g.health = { style = 'float' }\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean -u minimal.lua\n:checkhealth\n; Should open a centered window.\n:h 'comments'\n:checkhealth\n; Should open in the top-left corner.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe floating window should always be in the same place: at the cursor, in the middle, as a \"dropdown\" as it currently is, doesn't matter.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nnightly\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux, Fedora 43\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuilt from source",
